# Storage Module Rules

## Device validation — always first
```go
if err := kexec.MustBeBlockDevice(device); err != nil {
    return nil, err
}
```

## Command pattern
```go
// CORRECT
res, err := kexec.Run(ctx, 30*time.Second, "mdadm", "--detail", device)

// WRONG — never do this
cmd := exec.Command("sh", "-c", "mdadm --detail "+device)
```

## Btrfs snapshots
- Always use `btrfs subvolume snapshot -r` (read-only) for backups
- Store snapshots under `<mount>/<subvol>/.snapshots/`
- Call `EnsureSnapshotDir()` before creating snapshots

## LVM SSD cache
- Cache pool on NVMe/fast device: `lvcreate --type cache-pool`
- Use `--cachepolicy smq` (Stochastic Multi-Queue)
- Cache must be on different PV than data LV

## mdadm
- Always pass `--run` to `mdadm --create` to avoid interactive prompt
- Scrub with `echo check > /sys/block/md0/md/sync_action`
